						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in Survey No. 392/2, by the side of the east track leading to Koppukoṇḍa village.</p>						

						<p>17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This undated record may be assigned to 17th century on the basis of the palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It states that this pillar obviously the one bearing inscription is a boundary pillar between the village Vemṭarāya and Doṇḍapāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
